<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h1 class="panel-title"><%= "#{@sentence.tense.capitalize} #{@sentence.tense_modifier.humanize}" %></h1>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <div class="timeline">
	<div class="before-meter">
	<%= fa_icon "clock-o 3x" %>
	</div>
	<div class="meter-container animate">
		<div class="meter">
		  <div class="now">
			<%= fa_icon "map-marker 2x"%>
			<span class="marker-label">Now</span>
		  </div>
		  <div class="future">
			<%= fa_icon "map-marker 2x"%>
			<span class="marker-label">Future</span>
		  </div>
		  <span style="width: 12%; margin-left: 65%;"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	</div>
	</div>
	<ul class="list-group">
		<li class="list-group-item">
			<h4 class="panel-title">Uses</h4>
		</li>
		<li class="list-group-item">
		An action or state that started and is predicted to continue up to some moment in the future.
			<ul class="uses">
				<li>Usually focuses on the duration of the action.</li>
				<li>May also give context to the future situation.</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li class="list-group-item">
		<h4 class="panel-title">Examples</h4>
		</li>
		<li class="list-group-item">
		<ul class="eg-list">
			<li class="eg">
				<span>"Next year my dad will have been teaching for 25 years."</span><br>
				<span class="eg-explanation">(Focus on the duration of my dad teaching one year in the future)</span>
			</li>
			<li class="eg">
				<span>"You will probably want to stretch your legs after the flight because you will have been sitting on the plane for so long."</span><br>
				<span class="eg-explanation">(Context â€“ explains why you will want to stretch)</span>
			</li>
		</ul>
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>





